<subSubSection id="169E978168D189D9086F433C7547599C" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="716C6D0BC09E5F13F290F95CA3282F59" pageNumber="769">
Etymology L 
<taxonomicName id="233B15FA2276E26D606E3F968B3A7740" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34070" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole tristis (Smith)" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole tristis (Smith)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="769" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tristis">tristis</taxonomicName>
, sad, allusion unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B607D2B46DDE24619E8333E4B18D3D33" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="962D757475A6920686B342EEC5B2F789" pageNumber="769">
Diagnosis A medium-sized reddish-yellow (major) or yellowish brown (minor) member of the 
<taxonomicName id="E091C505B873F04FCFBF22E06EA04980" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34070" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole tristis (Smith)" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole tristis (Smith)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="769" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tristis">tristis</taxonomicName>
group whose major has very prominent subangulate pronotal humerus, swollen hind femora, diamond-shaped postpetiolar node with subangulate margins, small rounded subpostpetiolar process, and foveolate and opaque gastral tergite.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="59993FD98A4AD9E359F85713242778CA" type="description">
<paragraph id="45DD208FF81EB0A6523A3DA07EDFA73F" pageNumber="769">
Minor: large ovoid postpetiolar node, prominent convex subpostpetiolar process, and foveolate and opaque gastral tergites. Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="1DA7C4D7EE6433D74425E7DBA79D21B7" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33606" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole balzani Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole balzani Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="769" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balzani">balzani</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="542BD7BA6BAC2BE374A13EAACF6E5507" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33734" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole fabricator (Smith)" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole fabricator (Smith)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="769" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fabricator">fabricator</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="AB90E048C83BDCCC1DA133C7D9143A21" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182060" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole nigella Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole nigella Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="769" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigella">nigella</taxonomicName>
